Position Summary 
The Global Marketing Campaign Director will plan and develop multi-channel, integrated marketing campaigns to align with corporate campaign strategy and objectives to build awareness, drive demand, accelerate pipeline, and support client expansion.
 The Global Marketing Campaign Director owns and manages the campaign process â€“ from setting campaign goals, defining the audience framework, creating campaign themes and messaging, building the campaign hierarchy and content mapping, and delivering marketing mix recommendation and program strategy.
 This requires a leader with demonstrated ability to drive strategy, and a proven understanding / experience combining high level, global marketing goals and overall campaign objectives and business KPIs. The ideal candidate will be an expert communicator and leader, be able to effectively work with cross-marketing functions to lead the planning process, as well as other stakeholders in management and sales . 
 Essential Duties and Responsibilities 
Leads the strategic planning and development of integrated campaign initiatives incorporating central marketing and field/regional input 
Creates campaigns that support marketing initiatives and goals through thoughtful and collaborative, proactive planning
 Work with product marketing, sales and other stakeholders to shape campaign goals, audience segmentation, themes and messaging and campaign hierarchy, and program strategy and marketing mix for a yearlong timeframe 
Document the responsibilities of various functions during the campaign planning process 
Coordinate with key functions as they fulfill the programs that comprise a campaign (reputation, demand creation, sales enablement, market intelligence) 
Act as an authority for questions on campaign priorities, responsibilities, resources and timing 
Partner with Marketing Leadership to define budgets, metrics and measures of success of campaigns ensuring alignment with marketing strategy roadmap 
Work with internal and external partners to manage status of projects, delivery against business goals, and track changes to marketing strategies 
Author briefs and lead team to initiate workflow process with the Creative team and/or external agencies 
Demonstrate diligence, attention to detail and establishment of best practices throughout the full marketing campaign life cycle 
Prepare Senior Leadership Team level presentations and plans on a regular basis 
Develop, grow, and maintain relationships with internal teams through exceptional collaboration and leadership 
Help manage and the lead the delivery of campaign artifacts, and all relevant campaign documentation in preparation for campaign launch 
Partner with Analytics team on campaign measurement reporting and insights generation 
